# Release Workflow

When the user asks to publish/release a new version:

1. **Update `CHANGELOG.md`**: add a new section for the version BEFORE committing. Follow the existing
   Keep a Changelog style (`## [x.y.z] - YYYY-MM-DD` with `### 新增 / 变更 / 修复` subsections) and add
   the compare link at the bottom. The release workflow auto-extracts this section into the GitHub
   release body via `body_path`, so the section heading version MUST match the tag (without the `v`).
2. **Update `APP_VERSION`** in `src/loader/version_check.h` to match the new tag version
3. Commit all changes
4. Push to `main`
5. Create and push a git tag (e.g. `v1.3.0`) to trigger the GitHub Actions release build
6. The tag version, `APP_VERSION`, the `CHANGELOG.md` section, and the commit should all be in sync

Example:
```c
// src/loader/version_check.h
#define APP_VERSION L"1.3.0"  // Must match the tag being created
```

```markdown
<!-- CHANGELOG.md -->
## [1.3.0] - 2026-06-15
### 新增
- ...

[1.3.0]: https://github.com/NEETLee/FH6FucousKeeper/compare/v1.2.1...v1.3.0
```
